  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Urgent WASH support with minor rehabilitation to sewage infrastructure for the vulnerable households and communities in Rural Ar-Raqqa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aim and task is to provide basic WASH services to people at risk within the highly neglected community of Sabkah/ Raqqa governorate. The area of intervention is still witnessing a steady number of returnees, but they are facing massive difficulties in resettling back into their community, due to the large scale of destruction caused by the conflict. The water networks in general (portable water and sewage wasterwater canals) in the area of intervention are heavily damaged and according to our assessment sewage wastewater and portable water are mixing with each other, within the network system. This current WASH situation exacerbates the spread of diseases and the health situation in general and it is just a matter of time before the impact becomes uncontrollable, without rapid intervention. In the area of Sabkha, 90% of the sewage system is damaged, leaking and not functioning. This urgent need will be addressed by providing minor rehabilitation for two sewage canals, in order to interlink the two most affected neighbourhoods with a functional sewage network system.  The overall target is to provide the affected host and returnee community with basic WASH services and to reduce the outbreaks of possible diseases caused by the currently leaking sewage network system.</narrative>
  </description>
